9/23/16 - Mark Katz memo: I met with Adam Doud with Wells Fargo.  Adam was formally with Falcon and has relocated to Denver.  He is one of 7 producers within Wells Fargo that is charged with finding real estate deals for HNW clients of the bank.  Adam and his team are working directly with the private wealth advisors across the country.  This groups seemslike they could be a good fit for some of our middle market deals, so please add to deal lists as appropriate. Right now, my team is actively searching for industrial, retail and multi-family deals from $4 million to $10 million. Because cap rates have compressed in the major markets and because the deals have to be able to absorb Wells Fargo's asset management fee, we are trying to identify higher cap rate opportunities in secondary markets or in secondary locations of the major markets. Our platform is not advocating value-add opportunities right now, unless that value-add is related to market rent adjustments that may be accessed in the near-term. Properties with significant vacancy are tough for the bank to recommend. Our clients are generally concerned with generating income and diversifying their equity/bond portfolios. Putting assets at risk trying to generate exceedingly high return is not the strategy.Our real estate asset management team at Wells is a national team. We consider ourselves an investment advisor to the high net worth clients in Wells Fargo's Private Bank. Our current assets under management exceeds $5.5 billion and is growing rapidly (two years ago AUM was $4.4 billion and the increase in AUM includes $1 billion of dispositions‰Û_so gross additions over the past two years totals $2 billion).We are not affiliated with Eastdil Secured (for those in your company who may be concerned about that) and we are not a broker (we don't participate in commissions). Also, we are not a proxy for Wells Fargo's various lending platforms. So there could be financing opportunities with HFF.I would appreciate your help getting me included on your various distribution lists and would look forward to the chance to meet the members of your team.
